WEBVTT

00:01.167 --> 00:03.235
I booked
a hotel suite.

00:03.237 --> 00:04.770
You did what?

00:04.772 --> 00:06.772
It's pretty close
to your apartment.

00:06.774 --> 00:10.009
You could run there,
run back.

00:10.011 --> 00:11.143
Why am I
running there?

00:11.145 --> 00:12.344
Booty calls.
Booty calls?

00:12.346 --> 00:14.613
And I'm running there
for booty calls?

00:14.615 --> 00:18.384
We're back in d.C. We're not
standing in the sun anymore.

00:18.386 --> 00:20.052
I'm not gonna live
in your apartment,

00:20.054 --> 00:23.589
I have things to do.
I'm busy. But...

00:23.591 --> 00:26.325
I did book a nice hotel suite
for booty calls.
Okay, no.

00:26.327 --> 00:28.727
See, we have to have
a conversation about --

00:28.729 --> 00:31.096
I don't do
booty calls, jake.

00:31.098 --> 00:33.665
That right there
refutes your statement.

00:33.667 --> 00:37.169
That right there
is a political booty call.

00:37.171 --> 00:38.637
I'll see you later.

00:40.373 --> 00:41.707
Olivia:
You look good...

00:41.709 --> 00:43.509
Healthy.

00:43.511 --> 00:45.811
I'm a vegetarian now.

00:45.813 --> 00:48.580
[ laughs ]
they took
meat away from me --

00:48.582 --> 00:51.250
The aides, the housekeeper,
my security detail.

00:51.252 --> 00:53.719
They all got together
with the doctors and --

00:53.721 --> 00:57.689
They won't even stop the car
for a drive-through burger.

00:57.691 --> 00:59.458
I'm a prisoner --
fascists.

00:59.460 --> 01:01.527
They care about you.
They want you to live.

01:01.529 --> 01:02.728
Sons of bitches.

01:04.764 --> 01:06.098
You look like crap.

01:07.400 --> 01:09.234
No, I don't.

01:09.236 --> 01:11.236
You could let a person know
you're back in town.

01:11.238 --> 01:12.371
You knew I was here.

01:12.373 --> 01:13.472
You could call a friend.

01:13.474 --> 01:15.140
Are we?

01:15.142 --> 01:17.342
Still friends?

01:17.344 --> 01:18.610
I need a favor.

01:18.612 --> 01:20.345
I don't do favors
for the white house anymore.

01:20.347 --> 01:24.316
Then think of it as less
of a favor, more of a job.

01:24.318 --> 01:28.120
I  <i>definitely</i>don't work
for the white house anymore.

01:28.122 --> 01:30.222
Mm. Thing is...

01:30.224 --> 01:31.290
You already are.

01:32.293 --> 01:34.660
At least, if someone
were to take a look

01:34.662 --> 01:36.228
At your corporate
bank account,

01:36.230 --> 01:38.263
They'd think you were,
because they'd see

01:38.265 --> 01:40.766
That a considerable sum
has been deposited there

01:40.768 --> 01:44.803
By the United States government
for services rendered.

01:44.805 --> 01:46.772
You can't think
I'm above

01:46.774 --> 01:49.575
Calling in
a few favors at the I.R.S.

01:49.577 --> 01:51.443
You're blackmailing me?

01:51.445 --> 01:53.245
Blackmail!

01:53.247 --> 01:54.880
[ clears throat ]

01:54.882 --> 01:56.615
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

01:56.617 --> 01:59.151
James and lisa elliot --
are attending
the state of the union

01:59.153 --> 02:01.753
As the president's
guests of honor --
a living testament

02:01.755 --> 02:03.622
To his newfound commitment
to gun control.

02:03.624 --> 02:05.824
And?
They've missed
two flights from new mexico,

02:05.826 --> 02:07.826
And they're not returning
our calls.

02:07.828 --> 02:09.495
And the state
of the union is --

02:09.497 --> 02:10.796
Is tomorrow night.
Mm-hmm.

02:14.734 --> 02:18.871
Cyrus, you know
I'm not afraid of the I.R.S.

02:20.773 --> 02:23.308
I'll tell him...

02:23.310 --> 02:24.710
You call every day.

02:25.778 --> 02:30.849
I'll tell him you call,
asking about him every day,

02:30.851 --> 02:33.485
That you're pining for him.

02:35.355 --> 02:37.789
Sorry to be
such a bastard, liv.

02:39.759 --> 02:44.763
Craving meat really brings out
the worst in me.

02:53.706 --> 02:55.607
James elliot
is a real, live war hero.

02:55.609 --> 02:57.743
Escaped from
a taliban p.O.W. Camp,

02:57.745 --> 02:59.845
Hiked 27 miles
over the hindu kush mountains,

02:59.847 --> 03:01.680
Without shoes or water,
to reach safety.

03:01.682 --> 03:02.848
A total badass.
Right, huck?

03:02.850 --> 03:04.750
James met lisa
when he came to speak

03:04.752 --> 03:06.818
To her first-grade class
at red hawk elementary

03:06.820 --> 03:08.453
About two years before
the shooting.

03:08.455 --> 03:09.621
All those kids.

03:09.623 --> 03:11.823
Lisa saved
at least 50 lives.

03:11.825 --> 03:14.760
Led five girls trapped
in the line of fire to safety.

03:14.762 --> 03:16.195
46 minutes
after the shooting started,

03:16.197 --> 03:17.396
She took a bullet
to her spine.

03:17.398 --> 03:18.830
Paralyzed her
from the waist down.

03:18.832 --> 03:20.566
He took her to all those
funerals -- how many?

03:20.568 --> 03:23.635
29. The tabloids called her
"the angel of the mesa."

03:23.637 --> 03:25.437
Six months after physical
therapy, she was well enough --

03:25.439 --> 03:26.772
For a fairytale wedding.

03:26.774 --> 03:28.740
It was covered worldwide --
they told every reporter

03:28.742 --> 03:30.809
They were dedicating their lives
to getting guns off the street.

03:30.811 --> 03:32.244
And to each other.

03:32.246 --> 03:34.313
¶ ...At a guy who stuck out
in the crowd ¶

03:34.315 --> 03:36.215
[ doorbell rings ]

03:36.217 --> 03:38.483
¶ he had the kind of body
that would shame adonis ¶

03:38.485 --> 03:39.985
[ knock on door ]

03:39.987 --> 03:42.754
¶ and a face
that would make any man proud ¶

03:42.756 --> 03:44.523
Hello?

03:44.525 --> 03:45.691
Everyone loves them.

03:45.693 --> 03:48.327
I love them.
They're perfect.

03:48.329 --> 03:49.895
They about to be the most
high-profile guests of honor

03:49.897 --> 03:51.396
At the state of the union,

03:51.398 --> 03:53.732
So why didn't they
get on their plane this morning?

03:53.734 --> 03:55.801
One more insult
and I will kill you!

03:55.803 --> 03:56.902
Like hell you will!

03:56.904 --> 03:58.837
Get away from me!
Lisa!

03:58.839 --> 03:59.838
Lisa: [ grunts ]

04:00.540 --> 04:02.507
Suck on that,

04:02.509 --> 04:03.809
You stupid son of a --

04:03.811 --> 04:05.544
Hey!

04:05.546 --> 04:07.980
Thank you. I think
we've had enough, right?

04:07.982 --> 04:10.282
I'm sick and tired of being
the guy to make sure

04:10.284 --> 04:12.517
The lady in the wheelchair
gets whatever she wants,

04:12.519 --> 04:15.687
Whenever she wants it --
that's why.
Oh, here we go again.

04:15.689 --> 04:19.391
I'm the bitch
who somehow came up with

04:19.393 --> 04:20.759
The crazy idea
to get shot in the spine.

04:20.761 --> 04:22.694
That wheelchair
made you a star.

04:22.696 --> 04:24.830
Now, that wheelchair
is your freaking throne.

04:24.832 --> 04:27.699
It's like you sit in there
and you rule over your little...

04:27.701 --> 04:29.401
Paralyzed kingdom.

04:29.403 --> 04:30.602
You're such a whiner.

04:30.604 --> 04:32.304
I'm a whiner?
<i>I'm</i> a whiner?

04:32.306 --> 04:33.972
I was in a p.O.W. Camp
for two years.

04:33.974 --> 04:35.841
Oh, my god, will you stop it
with the p.O.W. Camp already?

04:35.843 --> 04:37.009
Whiner!
Okay, that's enough.

04:37.011 --> 04:39.645
I was tortured
by the taliban.

04:39.647 --> 04:41.046
"oh, I was
in a p.O.W. Camp.

04:41.048 --> 04:42.514
I was tortured
by the talibwan."

04:42.516 --> 04:43.849
What is your point,
james?

04:43.851 --> 04:49.755
Let's pause --
I was tortured by the taliban,
and it was better than this.

04:49.757 --> 04:51.023
The taliban
is better than you!

04:51.025 --> 04:52.691
That is it,
you son of a --

04:52.693 --> 04:55.694
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait!
I am the only one who talks!

04:57.730 --> 05:00.599
Just about 30 hours
from now,

05:00.601 --> 05:02.868
The president
of the United States of america

05:02.870 --> 05:05.837
Is going to stand up and give
the state of the union address.

05:05.839 --> 05:07.839
He'll be discussing
gun control.

05:07.841 --> 05:09.675
To do that, he needs
to point to the two of you,

05:09.677 --> 05:11.443
Because despite
whatever is happening here,

05:11.445 --> 05:13.912
You are the face of gun control
to the american people.

05:13.914 --> 05:16.581
So the president needs
your asses in those seats.

05:16.583 --> 05:18.750
The law depends on in.
Lives depend on it.

05:18.752 --> 05:21.753
So let's knock off
the bickering, pack our bags,

05:21.755 --> 05:23.855
And go serve our country,
shall we?

05:29.629 --> 05:30.696
You can't do this.
Can't do what?

05:30.698 --> 05:34.333
The centerpiece of
your state of the union address.

05:34.335 --> 05:35.033
Why not?

05:35.035 --> 05:36.702
Because we're republicans.

05:36.704 --> 05:38.403
You held your tongue
on equal pay.

05:38.405 --> 05:40.105
Yes, and then
you nominated a democrat

05:40.107 --> 05:41.773
To be
your attorney general.

05:41.775 --> 05:43.709
Cy, lizzie's just trying
to keep the party together.

05:43.711 --> 05:47.679
That's the speech.
Why isn't the president here
to defend this himself?

05:47.681 --> 05:50.515
Because he's not at your
beck and call like this one.

05:50.517 --> 05:51.717
All right.
That is enough.

05:51.719 --> 05:53.518
You made your point.

05:53.520 --> 05:55.087
Stand and clap, andrew.

05:55.089 --> 05:56.621
That's your job
tomorrow night --

05:56.623 --> 05:57.889
Stand and clap.

05:57.891 --> 06:01.059
Cyrus...

06:01.061 --> 06:02.127
Where's the president?

06:02.129 --> 06:04.963
Busy.
The president is busy.

06:08.701 --> 06:09.968
[ knock on glass ]

06:09.970 --> 06:11.870
Yes, dave?

06:11.872 --> 06:13.839
The first lady
would like her chips, sir.

06:18.811 --> 06:19.811
Thank you, sir.

06:29.455 --> 06:30.689
Here you go, ma'am.

06:30.691 --> 06:33.859
Ah, thank you, dave.
[ sighs ]

06:33.861 --> 06:35.694
Mmm.

06:37.630 --> 06:40.432
[ crunches ]

06:47.573 --> 06:50.709
[ camera shutter clicking ]

06:57.950 --> 07:01.620
Man: Has the first lady
been diagnosed by doctors,

07:01.622 --> 07:04.956
The first lady is grieving,
jim, not crazy.

07:04.958 --> 07:07.559
Stepping down
to care for his wife?

07:07.561 --> 07:09.761
<i>Carol, the president --</i>
<i>this is bad, cy.</i>

07:09.763 --> 07:11.863
Not for
potato chip sales.
Don't joke.

07:11.865 --> 07:14.900
So you're saying mrs. Grant
hasn't sought medical help.
No, carol.

07:14.902 --> 07:17.102
Well, then, how can you be sure
of her mental health?

07:17.104 --> 07:18.804
Easy, jim.
I compared her to you.

07:18.806 --> 07:19.805
<i>[ laughter ]</i>

07:19.807 --> 07:21.006
See? She's funny.

07:21.008 --> 07:22.941
She's just
adding fuel to the fire.

07:24.076 --> 07:26.545
Just trying to lighten the mood
in here, jim.

07:26.547 --> 07:28.046
No hard feelings.
Next question.

07:28.048 --> 07:30.449
Come on, abby. Don't dodge me.
These are serious questions.

07:30.451 --> 07:32.584
She could shut this whole thing
down with something like

07:32.586 --> 07:34.553
"just because a private moment
has been made public

07:34.555 --> 07:36.087
Doesn't give us
the right to pass judgment."

07:36.089 --> 07:37.789
Don't tell me
how to run my people.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.891
Just tell me I don't have to
worry about the elliots.

07:39.893 --> 07:43.195
America's sweethearts
hate each other --

07:43.197 --> 07:46.064
Like, really deeply hate each
other -- and I totally get why.

07:46.066 --> 07:48.900
They're horrible people,
cyrus -- both of them.
But you'll fix them.

07:48.902 --> 07:50.235
<i>I'm afraid that's all</i>
<i>the questions we have</i>
<i>time for right now.</i>

07:50.237 --> 07:51.603
Got to go.

07:53.206 --> 07:54.873
Watch your tone.
Less combative.

07:54.875 --> 07:56.575
Don't add fuel
to the fire.

07:56.577 --> 07:58.777
Just because a private moment
has been made public

07:58.779 --> 08:00.946
Doesn't give us the right
to pass judgment.

08:00.948 --> 08:02.781
Got it.
Good.

08:04.684 --> 08:06.151
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

08:06.153 --> 08:07.752
I need
everything you can get me

08:07.754 --> 08:09.754
On the murders of
harrison wright and adnan salif.

08:09.756 --> 08:12.657
Paperwork,
crime-scene photos -- all of it.

08:12.659 --> 08:14.860
I looked it over myself.
That investigation was clean.

08:14.862 --> 08:17.128
"clean" and "factual"
are very different things.

08:17.130 --> 08:19.664
Those two made it all the way
from d.C. To arizona

08:19.666 --> 08:21.900
Before ivan yushkin
tracked them down and shot them?

08:21.902 --> 08:24.269
Fine, but I want to see
the paper trail for myself.

08:24.271 --> 08:27.072
Well, noble of you, but
right now, I've really
got a lot on my plate.

08:27.074 --> 08:28.840
[ car door opens, closes ]

08:28.842 --> 08:30.609
Rowan
was at wright's funeral,

08:30.611 --> 08:33.278
And I don't think he was there
to be a supportive dad.

08:33.280 --> 08:35.947
I'm about to go through
a senate confirmation hearing,

08:35.949 --> 08:39.050
And I don't think
being a known associate
of a prolific assassin

08:39.052 --> 08:40.886
Is gonna be great
for my chances.

08:44.624 --> 08:47.659
Fine.
I'll do what I can.

08:47.661 --> 08:49.828
Can I go now, please?

09:00.740 --> 09:02.908
Hey.

09:02.910 --> 09:04.276
Hey.

09:04.278 --> 09:06.878
Liv's back from new mexico
with the elliots.

09:10.149 --> 09:11.917
Apparently,
they're awful.

09:11.919 --> 09:14.286
Just horrible, awful people
who hate each other.

09:14.288 --> 09:15.987
That's what
the problem is.

09:20.893 --> 09:23.562
So liv's putting
them in adjoining
rooms at the hay-adams,

09:23.564 --> 09:25.030
And she's doing
their press for them,

09:25.032 --> 09:26.698
And she asked us
to babysit.

09:29.735 --> 09:33.972
Because working together
is what we do best.

09:33.974 --> 09:37.576
Look, you don't have to
treat me like this.

09:37.578 --> 09:38.810
Yes, I do.

09:40.913 --> 09:42.314
[ keyboard clacking ]

09:44.884 --> 09:47.185
Olivia: The elliots
are a remarkable couple

09:47.187 --> 09:48.753
Who serve
to remind us all

09:48.755 --> 09:50.822
Of the necessity
of stricter gun-control laws,

09:50.824 --> 09:53.024
Something I know the president
cares deeply about.

09:53.026 --> 09:54.059
Speaking of the president,

09:54.061 --> 09:55.660
You've worked for him
in the past.

09:55.662 --> 09:57.596
What do you make of
the state of the first family?

09:57.598 --> 09:59.998
Well, I don't work
at the white house currently,

10:00.000 --> 10:03.301
But I do feel that just because
a private moment is made public

10:03.303 --> 10:05.103
<i>Doesn't give us the liberty</i>
<i>to pass judgment.</i>

10:05.105 --> 10:06.671
<i>In fact, I think</i>

10:06.673 --> 10:07.906
<i>Where we should be</i>
<i>focusing our priorities --</i>

10:07.908 --> 10:09.941
"just because a private moment
is made public

10:09.943 --> 10:12.010
Doesn't give us the liberty
to pass judgment"?

10:12.012 --> 10:13.778
I thought
you could use the help.

10:13.780 --> 10:15.814
<i>You</i> don't
work here anymore, liv.

10:15.816 --> 10:18.617
<i>I</i> do, and I will do things
my own way,

10:18.619 --> 10:22.621
You don't know everything.
You don't know anything.

10:22.623 --> 10:24.356
Harrison dies.
The firm falls apart.

10:24.358 --> 10:26.925
Huck and quinn were incest-ing
all over the office

10:26.927 --> 10:29.861
For god knows how long,
and you had no idea.

10:29.863 --> 10:31.830
Huck and what?
Uh-huh. Yeah.

10:38.871 --> 10:39.938
Mmm, mmm.

10:42.642 --> 10:46.077
Fried chicken.
Chef will make fried chicken.

10:46.079 --> 10:49.014
All you got to do is pick up
the phone and ask, and bam --

10:49.016 --> 10:51.049
Fried chicken,
southern-fried, real.

10:51.051 --> 10:52.384
You want some?

10:52.386 --> 10:54.052
No, thank you.
Mellie, I need --
[ chuckles ]

10:54.054 --> 10:56.888
I'd like to have
a discussion with you about --

10:56.890 --> 10:58.957
Mellie, ma'am, this photo
of you looking crazy

10:58.959 --> 11:02.027
Is in every paper in america,
and we have a huge problem

11:02.029 --> 11:04.996
Because
the state of the union --
cyrus!

11:04.998 --> 11:07.799
Someone took this of me
at jerry's grave?

11:07.801 --> 11:09.334
I'm sorry.

11:09.336 --> 11:11.002
We don't know how they got
through with all the security.

11:11.004 --> 11:14.339
It should be private.
You should have your privacy.

11:14.341 --> 11:15.807
But it's out there,

11:15.809 --> 11:18.710
And now the state of the union
is in 24 hours.

11:18.712 --> 11:19.878
You want me to go
to the state of the union?

11:19.880 --> 11:21.346
Yes.

11:21.348 --> 11:23.915
It'll shut this down,
keep the focus on the speech.

11:23.917 --> 11:26.685
If you don't go, your absence,
your "state of mind"

11:26.687 --> 11:28.887
Will be all
anyone will be talking about.

11:30.856 --> 11:34.893
[ chuckles ]

11:34.895 --> 11:37.262
Mellie.
[ laughing ]

11:39.865 --> 11:44.302
Oh, honey, baby,
do you actually think

11:44.304 --> 11:47.305
I give a damn what
anyone thinks of me anymore?
Mellie.

11:47.307 --> 11:48.773
And for you to come here

11:48.775 --> 11:50.809
And pretend that this
is all about me

11:50.811 --> 11:53.211
When really --
let's face it, baby --

11:53.213 --> 11:54.913
This is all about you.

11:54.915 --> 11:57.182
This is
"the fitzgerald grant show"

11:57.184 --> 11:58.883
Staring fitzgerald grant.

11:58.885 --> 12:00.819
And you just want me
to play my part --

12:00.821 --> 12:03.421
The costar, the dutiful wife
who smiles and applauds

12:03.423 --> 12:06.091
And looks so proud of you
and doesn't eat chicken

12:06.093 --> 12:08.126
Or wear sweatpants
or hang out on graves.

12:08.128 --> 12:11.396
[ laughs ]

12:11.398 --> 12:15.800
[ chewing, chuckling ]

12:25.945 --> 12:27.245
You're supposed to be
a vegetarian.

12:27.247 --> 12:30.081
So I die of a heart attack --
big deal.

12:32.351 --> 12:34.786
Least I'll be with james.

12:34.788 --> 12:37.756
[ sighs ]

12:37.758 --> 12:40.325
It's not the same --

12:40.327 --> 12:44.229
My child, your husband.

12:44.231 --> 12:46.097
[ sighs ]

12:46.099 --> 12:49.234
It's not the same.

12:50.936 --> 12:54.105
I keep hearing that.

12:57.076 --> 12:59.511
The loss of a child
is greater.

12:59.513 --> 13:02.881
I resent that,
never having lost a child.

13:04.450 --> 13:09.187
I resent having to feel like
losing the love of my life --

13:09.189 --> 13:15.193
The only someone who ever made
me feel like I was truly me --

13:15.195 --> 13:20.899
Is less of a loss,
is smaller than your loss.

13:23.402 --> 13:26.905
[ voice breaking ]
I'm now broken. I'm now not me.

13:26.907 --> 13:30.175
I'm now forever changed.
I'm undone.

13:30.177 --> 13:32.944
A broken heart
is a broken heart --

13:32.946 --> 13:35.480
To take a measure
is cruelty.

13:42.087 --> 13:44.856
I'm not going tomorrow.

13:45.858 --> 13:47.826
[ sighs ]

13:47.828 --> 13:48.960
I'm not
putting on a dress.

13:48.962 --> 13:50.195
I'm not
waving for the cameras.

13:50.197 --> 13:52.197
I'm done, cyrus.
I'm through.

13:59.939 --> 14:02.307
And we are not the same.

14:16.155 --> 14:18.523
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

14:20.993 --> 14:23.394
I wasn't sure
you'd make it.

14:23.396 --> 14:24.596
To my office?

14:24.598 --> 14:25.997
I know you've got
a lot on your plate.

14:25.999 --> 14:28.032
I'm fine.

14:29.068 --> 14:30.602
So...

14:30.604 --> 14:31.970
Senate-confirmation
hearing

14:31.972 --> 14:34.172
For the office
of attorney general.

14:34.174 --> 14:36.074
[ clears throat ]
let's get started.

14:37.376 --> 14:38.910
What can you tell
this committee

14:38.912 --> 14:40.278
About the trial
of the molotov mistress?

14:40.280 --> 14:43.047
Aren't they gonna
ease into this a little,

14:43.049 --> 14:44.616
Ask me where
I went to college?

14:44.618 --> 14:47.085
Bryan: I understand you went
to dartmouth, mr. Rosen.

14:47.087 --> 14:48.386
So did I.

14:48.388 --> 14:52.257
Ah, it is, sir, as I have said,
a small college --

14:52.259 --> 14:54.926
Both: And yet
there are those who love it.

14:54.928 --> 14:56.661
[ both chuckle ]

14:56.663 --> 14:58.263
What can you tell
this committee

14:58.265 --> 15:00.498
About the trial of
the so-called molotov mistress?

15:00.500 --> 15:03.534
Abby: The most important vote on
the senate judiciary committee

15:03.536 --> 15:04.636
Is al watson.

15:04.638 --> 15:08.306
But if we can convince him,
we're home free.

15:08.308 --> 15:09.607
He's savage.

15:09.609 --> 15:11.609
You were fired, mr. Rosen --
correct? --

15:11.611 --> 15:14.312
For pursuing
some loony conspiracy theory

15:14.314 --> 15:15.914
About election rigging?

15:15.916 --> 15:17.982
I told you -- I left
to pursue another career.

15:17.984 --> 15:20.985
You left a prestigious job
as a United States attorney

15:20.987 --> 15:22.954
To teach
public high school?

15:22.956 --> 15:25.123
Michael jordan left the bulls
to play minor league baseball.

15:25.125 --> 15:27.992
You're comparing yourself
to michael jordan?!

15:27.994 --> 15:30.995
To anyone who's ever
followed a dream, senator.

15:36.602 --> 15:39.671
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

15:47.012 --> 15:49.547
So,
you like sports?

15:49.549 --> 15:50.949
No.

15:50.951 --> 15:52.150
Okay.

15:52.152 --> 15:53.952
How about a drink?
Do you drink?

15:55.087 --> 15:58.022
He was such a hero,
you know.

15:59.992 --> 16:01.626
I mean, all those years
as a p.O.W,

16:01.628 --> 16:05.263
And he comes homes without
a trace of bitterness,

16:05.265 --> 16:08.232
Which is hard
to believe now.

16:08.234 --> 16:09.734
But then...

16:09.736 --> 16:12.070
He was perfect.

16:12.072 --> 16:15.740
And he thought
I was perfect.

16:15.742 --> 16:18.409
[ sighs ]

16:18.411 --> 16:22.981
And we were in love.

16:22.983 --> 16:24.983
Before...

16:24.985 --> 16:27.018
All this.

16:29.388 --> 16:33.057
[ breathes deeply ]

16:33.059 --> 16:34.559
We were in love.

17:05.591 --> 17:08.126
[ cellphone ringing ]

17:11.697 --> 17:12.797
Liv.
Hey.

17:12.799 --> 17:14.565
Did I catch you
at a bad time?

17:14.567 --> 17:17.502
No. What's up?
Nothing.

17:17.504 --> 17:18.736
Is this
a booty call?

17:18.738 --> 17:21.105
No.

17:21.107 --> 17:22.640
There was no reason
for you to get a hotel room.

17:22.642 --> 17:26.744
I'm not gonna sleep in your bed
like some kept man.

17:26.746 --> 17:28.546
You were fine
staying with me.

17:28.548 --> 17:30.581
I was fine with it.
You should come back.

17:30.583 --> 17:32.817
Are you summoning me?
No.

17:34.486 --> 17:35.586
Possibly.

17:35.588 --> 17:37.588
You can't summon me.

17:37.590 --> 17:38.823
Get over here.

17:38.825 --> 17:40.758
You are not
in charge of me.

17:40.760 --> 17:42.693
You are not
in charge of <i>me.</i>

17:42.695 --> 17:44.629
I never said I was.
I did, however, let you know

17:44.631 --> 17:46.497
That I'm available
for booty calls --

17:46.499 --> 17:47.698
All the booty calls
you want.
[ sighs ]

17:47.700 --> 17:48.699
At my hotel.

17:48.701 --> 17:50.568
In room 207.

17:50.570 --> 17:52.670
I don't like this.

17:52.672 --> 17:55.206
Don't like it,
then.

17:58.410 --> 18:00.578
[ sighs ]

18:02.181 --> 18:03.714
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

18:20.566 --> 18:22.166
Elizabeth,
to what do I --

18:22.168 --> 18:24.168
[ door closes ]
why are you here?

18:24.170 --> 18:27.705
I know you won't believe me,
but I'm sorry.

18:27.707 --> 18:31.342
By a friend
in senator watson's office.

18:31.344 --> 18:33.678
It seems a copy
was sent to him this afternoon.

18:33.680 --> 18:35.546
Rosen?

18:35.548 --> 18:37.482
Domestic abuse?

18:37.484 --> 18:38.783
It's toxic,
cyrus.

18:38.785 --> 18:40.485
Watson moves forward
on this,

18:40.487 --> 18:42.787
And the president's entire
agenda comes crashing down.

18:42.789 --> 18:44.689
It's one brick
in a wall, liz.

18:44.691 --> 18:46.491
Let's not
get ahead of ourselves.

18:46.493 --> 18:49.494
A man who would nominate an
attorney general who beats women

18:49.496 --> 18:53.865
Or someone whose attention
isn't where it's supposed to be.

18:53.867 --> 18:56.868
Too busy caring
for his wife, perhaps.

18:57.903 --> 18:59.804
Have rosen decline
the nomination

18:59.806 --> 19:01.105
At tomorrow's hearing.

19:01.107 --> 19:02.874
It's the only choice.

19:05.444 --> 19:06.644
You're right.

19:06.646 --> 19:08.713
I don't believe
you're sorry at all.

19:17.222 --> 19:18.489
[ door closes ]

19:23.662 --> 19:25.563
But this is fabricated.

19:25.565 --> 19:27.832
You know this is fabricated.

19:27.834 --> 19:29.467
Olivia pope
had harrison plant this.

19:29.469 --> 19:31.569
He paid a girl
to say I beat her.
It doesn't matter.

19:31.571 --> 19:33.304
She's lying.
I never --
david.

19:33.306 --> 19:34.939
I thought you said
harrison wright buried this.

19:34.941 --> 19:36.874
I thought he did. I don't know
how anyone found it.

19:36.876 --> 19:39.510
It doesn't matter.
Someone did.

19:39.512 --> 19:42.647
The president likes you,
but it's over.

19:42.649 --> 19:43.848
I'm sorry.

19:46.818 --> 19:48.686
[ door closes ]
I'm sorry, david.

19:48.688 --> 19:49.754
Really.

19:52.558 --> 19:53.624
Thanks.

19:55.661 --> 19:57.295
Olivia pope.

19:57.297 --> 20:00.464
For all her talk
of white hats and doing good,

20:00.466 --> 20:02.667
She just gets
whatever she wants,

20:02.669 --> 20:04.802
And sometimes
you're just collateral damage.

20:04.804 --> 20:06.270
Admit it.

20:06.272 --> 20:08.239
Come on, you don't
work there anymore.

20:08.241 --> 20:10.441
She has no loyalty.

20:10.443 --> 20:12.376
She gets what she wants
because she's a winner,

20:12.378 --> 20:14.478
And she doesn't sit around
wondering whether or not

20:14.480 --> 20:18.316
We have to come up
with a statement.
Where are you going?

20:18.318 --> 20:19.617
I'm gonna go win.

20:22.854 --> 20:25.623
[ sighs ]

20:29.528 --> 20:30.695
Excuse me.

20:30.697 --> 20:33.698
Uh, can I get
a, uh --

20:33.700 --> 20:36.767
What is that?
Is that...Vodka?

20:36.769 --> 20:40.238
It's made from cow's milk,
apparently.

20:40.240 --> 20:41.839
Actually
kind of creamy.

20:43.942 --> 20:46.711
In fact,
can I have another, please?

20:46.713 --> 20:47.945
Thanks.

20:50.582 --> 20:52.383
Here.
[ clears throat ]

20:52.385 --> 20:53.751
Let me get those.

20:55.287 --> 20:57.755
No, no.
It's okay.

20:57.757 --> 21:00.891
I'm...
Not interested.

21:00.893 --> 21:02.560
Not that
I wouldn't be.

21:05.530 --> 21:06.864
I just --

21:06.866 --> 21:09.734
Oh.
You're, uh --

21:09.736 --> 21:12.036
You're with someone.
I get it.
No.

21:12.038 --> 21:14.705
Um, well...

21:14.707 --> 21:15.973
Not really.

21:21.747 --> 21:23.714
But...

21:23.716 --> 21:24.949
I can't.

21:24.951 --> 21:26.917
[ sighs ]

21:31.823 --> 21:33.691
It's okay.

21:40.632 --> 21:41.699
Mmm.

21:41.701 --> 21:43.934
This is delicious.
[ laughs ]

21:43.936 --> 21:45.002
Good night.

21:51.810 --> 21:55.780
James and huck:
¶ oh, where we go,
you will always know ¶

21:55.782 --> 21:58.316
¶ that the army
goes rolling along ¶

21:58.318 --> 21:59.750
What the hell
are you doing?

21:59.752 --> 22:01.585
Singing the army song.
What the hell are you doing?

22:01.587 --> 22:02.586
Are you drunk?
No.

22:02.588 --> 22:05.556
Why don't you mind
your own business for once?

22:11.730 --> 22:14.398
I didn't know
what else to do, huck.

22:14.400 --> 22:16.500
I thought you'd want
to know about your family.

22:16.502 --> 22:19.103
I was trying to help you,
but I don't know why I bothered.

22:19.105 --> 22:21.339
We were never
a normal couple.

22:21.341 --> 22:23.641
You're always gonna be the guy
who pulled my teeth out.

22:23.643 --> 22:26.744
Because you couldn't mind
your own business.

22:26.746 --> 22:29.647
You could never mind
your own business, quinn.

22:29.649 --> 22:31.882
And if I had
to do it again

22:31.884 --> 22:34.852
To teach you
that one very valuable lesson,

22:34.854 --> 22:36.087
I would.

22:38.857 --> 22:42.059
James:
[ screams ]

22:42.061 --> 22:43.594
[ groans ]

22:43.596 --> 22:44.962
God.

22:44.964 --> 22:46.797
You bitch.

22:48.600 --> 22:50.000
Lisa, why don't you
open this door

22:50.002 --> 22:51.769
So we can all have
a conversation?

22:51.771 --> 22:53.637
Lisa:
I'm not talking to him!
Lisa.

22:53.639 --> 22:56.407
Don't bother. Just
put me on the next
plane to abq. I'm done.

22:56.409 --> 22:57.641
James,
we're all just

22:57.643 --> 22:59.076
Gonna
take a minute here.

22:59.078 --> 23:01.812
I'm serious. Screw her
and screw gun control.

23:06.151 --> 23:08.686
What the hell
happened in there?
Ask huck.

23:08.688 --> 23:10.888
Maybe he'll sing you
a song about it.

23:16.828 --> 23:18.963
Huck, what's going on
with you and quinn?
Nothing.

23:18.965 --> 23:23.868
Do you want to tell me,
or am I gonna have to tell you?

23:26.571 --> 23:28.672
It was only --

23:28.674 --> 23:30.574
It was only
a couple of times.

23:31.777 --> 23:33.010
Huck,
look at me.

23:35.514 --> 23:37.014
Look at me.

23:42.888 --> 23:44.188
Huck --
I'm fine.

23:44.190 --> 23:45.556
Don't touch me.

23:55.934 --> 23:58.469
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

24:17.722 --> 24:20.558
Hawley, pennsylvania,
senator watson.

24:20.560 --> 24:23.661
I've been doing
some reading.

24:23.663 --> 24:24.795
Turn to page three.

24:24.797 --> 24:26.697
Or maybe just skip
right to the end

24:26.699 --> 24:27.998
Where we find
a couple million in bribes

24:28.000 --> 24:30.868
Tucked under the venison
in your garage freezer.

24:30.870 --> 24:32.470
This is blackmail.

24:32.472 --> 24:35.005
I like to think of it
as winning.

24:39.144 --> 24:41.145
[ indistinct talking ]

24:44.850 --> 24:48.786
Watson: David rosen has shown
himself to be highly qualified,

24:48.788 --> 24:50.154
<i>And I am confident</i>

24:50.156 --> 24:55.826
<i>And vote in favor of mr. Rosen</i>
<i>for attorney general.</i>

24:55.828 --> 24:57.628
What the hell is that?

24:57.630 --> 24:58.929
<i>Mr. Rosen,</i>
<i>when he appeared...</i>

24:58.931 --> 25:00.731
Get me watson's office
right now.

25:00.733 --> 25:02.166
<i>...He was very impressive.</i>

25:02.168 --> 25:04.001
Tonight, the president heads to
the capitol building

25:04.003 --> 25:05.669
For what insiders are suggesting

25:05.671 --> 25:07.771
Will be an historic
state of the union address.

25:07.773 --> 25:09.173
While rumors still swirl

25:09.175 --> 25:10.741
As to the mental health
of the first lady

25:10.743 --> 25:13.244
And the emotional state
of the entire first family,

25:13.246 --> 25:15.045
White house watchers are hoping
to catch a glimpse

25:15.047 --> 25:16.547
Of mellie grant tonight.

25:16.549 --> 25:17.848
Under siege
from his own party

25:17.850 --> 25:19.750
For his recent attempts
to reach across the aisle,

25:19.752 --> 25:22.286
Including what seems to be
an imminent confirmation

25:22.288 --> 25:24.588
Of democratic attorney general
david rosen,

25:24.590 --> 25:26.790
President grant
is expected to double down

25:26.792 --> 25:29.026
On several formerly
democratic causes,

25:29.028 --> 25:31.161
Most especially gun control.

25:33.164 --> 25:34.899
[ door opens ]

25:35.967 --> 25:38.102
[ door slams ]

25:38.104 --> 25:39.670
Good news or the usual?

25:39.672 --> 25:43.073
The elliots won't be attending
the pre-reception,

25:43.075 --> 25:44.775
Which means the cameras
won't catch them

25:44.777 --> 25:46.110
Going into the capitol,
which means that

25:46.112 --> 25:48.546
When the networks do
their intros tonight,

25:48.548 --> 25:50.981
There will be no b-roll
to go along with their stories

25:50.983 --> 25:53.684
Of true love triumphing
over the evil of guns.

25:53.686 --> 25:55.185
They're not gonna show.

25:55.187 --> 25:56.754
Liv's on it.

25:56.756 --> 25:57.888
[ scoffs ]

25:57.890 --> 26:00.591
You're not even
a little concerned?

26:00.593 --> 26:02.192
Oh, I'm concerned.

26:02.194 --> 26:05.029
[ sighs ]

26:05.031 --> 26:07.631
I'm concerned that
fitzgerald grant's second term

26:07.633 --> 26:09.266
As president
of these United States

26:09.268 --> 26:11.201
Is about to be derailed

26:11.203 --> 26:13.938
Because his wife won't stop
eating fried chicken long enough

26:13.940 --> 26:15.639
To put on a cocktail dress.

26:15.641 --> 26:17.141
I'm concerned that

26:17.143 --> 26:19.677
Our enemies are sharpening
their long knives

26:19.679 --> 26:21.345
For the rapidly
approaching moment

26:21.347 --> 26:23.981
When it becomes politically
acceptable to point out

26:23.983 --> 26:26.717
That maybe, just maybe,
the president's home life

26:26.719 --> 26:28.852
Has begun to affect
his decision-making.

26:28.854 --> 26:31.221
I am concerned that

26:31.223 --> 26:35.259
Everything I've devoted
far more of my soul to

26:35.261 --> 26:39.763
Than has ever been right
or healthy or appropriate

26:39.765 --> 26:43.200
Is about to come crashing down
on a 16-year-old's grave.

26:43.202 --> 26:46.804
But, no, I am not concerned
that olivia pope will fail.

26:46.806 --> 26:51.842
I am never concerned
that olivia pope will fail.

26:51.844 --> 26:54.078
The elliots will be
at the state of the union.

26:54.080 --> 26:56.814
Mellie, not so much.

27:05.824 --> 27:07.992
What are you doing?
Why aren't you dressed?

27:07.994 --> 27:09.860
James:
I can't do this anymore.

27:09.862 --> 27:10.828
I'm sorry.

27:10.830 --> 27:12.329
I just can't.

27:16.835 --> 27:18.702
Quinn, open the door.

27:22.374 --> 27:25.976
James, lisa,
what you need is a divorce.

27:25.978 --> 27:27.845
What?
We can't.

27:27.847 --> 27:29.713
You <i>can.</i>
<i>Get a divorce.</i>

27:29.715 --> 27:31.915
Get out before
this kills you both.

27:31.917 --> 27:33.917
You'll have to pay back
the advance

27:33.919 --> 27:36.053
Sell the house,
take the loss.

27:36.055 --> 27:38.656
But I will spin this
for you.

27:38.658 --> 27:40.324
I will make sure that,
when it's over,

27:40.326 --> 27:42.826
Off of individual speaking
engagements.

27:42.828 --> 27:44.795
I will keep
the public on your side --

27:44.797 --> 27:46.130
Both of your sides.

27:46.132 --> 27:48.332
I will give you a way out.
I can do that.

27:48.334 --> 27:50.267
Unless you're only
staying together for the fame,

27:50.269 --> 27:51.802
In which case
you deserve each other

27:51.804 --> 27:53.904
And I wish you both
a long and miserable life.

28:12.157 --> 28:14.925
Mrs. Grant?

28:18.830 --> 28:20.097
Abby: Mrs. Grant?

28:20.099 --> 28:21.865
[ sighs ] I don't know
who you are,

28:21.867 --> 28:23.901
But you are obviously some sort
of desperate hail mary

28:23.903 --> 28:25.269
From my husband
or from cyrus

28:25.271 --> 28:28.172
Who thinks [chuckling]
there is a chance in hell

28:28.174 --> 28:29.940
Of getting me to
put on that stupid dress

28:29.942 --> 28:31.809
And go to
that stupid speech.

28:31.811 --> 28:35.079
I'm not interested in whatever
it is you came here to say,

28:35.081 --> 28:37.347
So save it and go away.

28:37.349 --> 28:39.249
It's not happening.

28:46.458 --> 28:48.258
Children die, mrs. Grant.

28:48.260 --> 28:49.860
I don't have children,

28:49.862 --> 28:51.862
So you may think it's horrible
for me to say that,

28:51.864 --> 28:53.497
And maybe it is,
but it's also a fact

28:53.499 --> 28:55.132
That of all
the millions of americans

28:55.134 --> 28:56.800
Who will be watching
and listening to

28:56.802 --> 28:58.502
The state of the union address
tonight,

28:58.504 --> 28:59.870
There are thousands
of people out there

28:59.872 --> 29:00.971
Whose children have died,

29:00.973 --> 29:02.339
Just like yours.

29:02.341 --> 29:06.210
Flipping through trash
and eating potato chips.

29:06.212 --> 29:07.945
They got
three days to grieve --

29:07.947 --> 29:09.313
Three weeks
if they were lucky --

29:09.315 --> 29:10.781
Or they would
lose their jobs.

29:10.783 --> 29:13.851
And make no mistake,
mrs. Grant, you have a job.

29:13.853 --> 29:15.886
You're the first lady
of the United States,

29:15.888 --> 29:17.855
And it might not pay,
but it is a job.

29:17.857 --> 29:19.957
And if jackie kennedy
could be in a car

29:19.959 --> 29:21.225
With her husband's brains

29:21.227 --> 29:23.093
Splattered
across her lap one minute

29:23.095 --> 29:24.428
And standing next to l.B.J.

29:24.430 --> 29:26.930
As he was sworn in
to replace her dead husband

29:26.932 --> 29:28.432
Just 99 minutes later,

29:28.434 --> 29:31.468
You can put on a dress
and stand in your private box

29:31.470 --> 29:33.504
And show all the people
in our nation

29:33.506 --> 29:36.373
Who share the horrible burden
of losing a child with you

29:36.375 --> 29:38.842
That the first family
may be devastated,

29:38.844 --> 29:41.145
But it has not forgotten
the american people

29:41.147 --> 29:43.781
And who need to see
that you're okay,

29:43.783 --> 29:45.849
Whether or not
it's the truth.

29:53.958 --> 29:56.026
That is what
I came here to say.

29:58.563 --> 30:00.831
A-and
I'll let myself out.

30:09.875 --> 30:13.944
From here an aide will take you
to your seats.

30:13.946 --> 30:16.146
This is the finish line.

30:19.083 --> 30:22.019
Sorry, ma'am.
Gonna need you to stay put.

30:27.292 --> 30:28.292
Mr. President.

30:28.294 --> 30:29.593
Abby.

30:29.595 --> 30:31.929
Olivia.
Hi, liv.

30:31.931 --> 30:33.997
This is
james and lisa elliot.

30:33.999 --> 30:36.500
Fitz: Thank you both so much for
your service to your country.

30:36.502 --> 30:41.171
Mr. And mrs. Elliot,
I'll take you to your seats.

30:50.982 --> 30:52.049
Well.

30:52.051 --> 30:53.483
Well.

30:53.485 --> 30:54.618
Thank you
for the elliots.

30:54.620 --> 30:56.887
Not a problem.

30:56.889 --> 30:58.088
Ms. Whelan, we need
the president's final remarks

30:58.090 --> 30:59.156
For the teleprompter.

30:59.158 --> 31:00.424
Got them right here.

31:00.426 --> 31:03.260
No.
Wait just a second.

31:03.262 --> 31:04.595
Can ms. Pope and I
have the room?

31:04.597 --> 31:06.029
That is not necessary.

31:06.031 --> 31:07.464
Can ms. Pope and I
have the room?

31:18.343 --> 31:20.310
That was not a good idea.

31:20.312 --> 31:21.478
Gabby will be fine.

31:24.082 --> 31:25.949
I need to hear
what you think.

31:25.951 --> 31:28.986
Before I go out there
and talk to the country,

31:28.988 --> 31:30.621
I need to know
what you think.

31:30.623 --> 31:32.289
No.

31:34.425 --> 31:37.928
Don't you think you owe me
at least this much?

31:40.999 --> 31:44.601
Man: Mr. Speaker, the president
of the United States!

31:44.603 --> 31:49.439
[ cheers and applause ]

31:49.441 --> 31:53.610
Fitz:
We honor the lives we've lost
in service to this great nation.

31:53.612 --> 31:55.178
[ applause ]

31:57.682 --> 32:01.418
But not every death
is a sacrifice.

32:01.420 --> 32:04.521
Not every death has meaning.

32:04.523 --> 32:07.291
Just ask lisa elliot,

32:07.293 --> 32:10.193
Who scooped up a first grader
named joelle brandt

32:10.195 --> 32:11.628
And carried her to safety,

32:11.630 --> 32:13.964
Only to watch her die

32:13.966 --> 32:18.702
From one of the 102 rounds
unloaded at red hawk elementary.

32:31.649 --> 32:34.985
I wasn't planning on
talking about this tonight.

32:34.987 --> 32:36.453
It's fine.

32:36.455 --> 32:37.988
I know you.

32:37.990 --> 32:39.990
"it's fine"
never means it's fine.

32:39.992 --> 32:42.326
[ sighs ]

32:42.328 --> 32:44.061
Okay.

32:49.133 --> 32:50.634
This isn't right.

32:50.636 --> 32:52.102
It's not?

32:52.104 --> 32:53.170
It's not.

32:53.172 --> 32:57.307
It's not, um --

32:57.309 --> 32:59.343
It's not the speech
on my teleprompter.

32:59.345 --> 33:00.610
So tell me
how to fix it.

33:00.612 --> 33:02.346
And I can tell you
that right about now

33:02.348 --> 33:04.681
There are any number of staffers
having heart attacks,

33:04.683 --> 33:06.216
Wondering what I'm about to say.

33:06.218 --> 33:07.684
[ laughter ]

33:07.686 --> 33:10.420
No one is going to care about
james and lisa elliot

33:10.422 --> 33:13.457
If they're too busy wondering
about fitz and mellie grant.

33:13.459 --> 33:15.392
She's still grieving.

33:15.394 --> 33:17.527
The world knows
she's still grieving.

33:17.529 --> 33:19.463
So be honest.

33:19.465 --> 33:23.400
But here's the truth.

33:23.402 --> 33:30.340
My family and I have been
through something unspeakable.

33:30.342 --> 33:33.377
Something that no parent --
no human being --

33:33.379 --> 33:35.545
Should ever have to experience.

33:39.784 --> 33:43.487
<i>And we are, all of us,</i>

33:43.489 --> 33:46.757
<i>Dealing with our loss</i>
<i>in the best ways we know how --</i>

33:46.759 --> 33:51.661
Me...
Our daughter, karen...

33:51.663 --> 33:54.631
Our little son, teddy...

33:54.633 --> 33:59.269
And my lovely, amazingly strong
wife, mellie,

33:59.271 --> 34:04.207
Who is here to support
our nation tonight.

34:04.209 --> 34:07.677
[ applause ]

34:10.314 --> 34:13.283
[ cheers and applause ]

34:18.289 --> 34:19.489
I was gonna wear blue,

34:19.491 --> 34:21.725
But I heard
the elliots are wearing blue,

34:21.727 --> 34:25.328
So I decided to go with red.

34:42.080 --> 34:45.816
My son jerry's death...

34:45.818 --> 34:49.219
Was a horrible fluke.

34:49.221 --> 34:51.721
But it was just that --
a fluke.

34:51.723 --> 34:53.423
An accident.

34:53.425 --> 34:54.758
A bacterial strain

34:54.760 --> 34:56.593
That we do not yet
have the capacity

34:56.595 --> 34:59.729
To keep
our loved ones safe from.

34:59.731 --> 35:03.633
But there were
thousands of people last year

35:03.635 --> 35:10.440
Who lost their lives
in a completely avoidable way.

35:10.442 --> 35:13.543
The right to bear arms --

35:13.545 --> 35:17.547
Set in stone in the constitution
by our founding fathers.

35:17.549 --> 35:22.886
So was slavery, by the way.

35:22.888 --> 35:28.125
The right to bear arms --
seems indisputable...

35:30.194 --> 35:33.363
...Until the shooter comes,

35:33.365 --> 35:37.434
<i>Until you're lisa elliot,</i>
<i>covered in blood,</i>

35:37.436 --> 35:43.440
Watching a little girl
take her last breath,

35:43.442 --> 35:46.610
Watching the light
go out of her eyes.

35:51.582 --> 35:55.552
<i>And that...</i>

35:55.554 --> 36:00.790
<i>That is where</i>
<i>the argument ends.</i>

36:00.792 --> 36:05.795
<i>That is when</i>
<i>the debate is over.</i>

36:10.902 --> 36:14.704
My son...

36:14.706 --> 36:17.174
My son is dead.

36:19.844 --> 36:22.345
And I ask you here tonight,

36:22.347 --> 36:25.715
Without a teleprompter,
without a speech,

36:25.717 --> 36:31.488
Without anything but my love
as a husband and a father...

36:31.490 --> 36:34.891
And an american,

36:34.893 --> 36:39.729
How many other people's children
are we going to let die

36:39.731 --> 36:43.300
Before we put a stop to this?

36:43.302 --> 36:46.503
[ cheers and applause ]

37:04.855 --> 37:06.456
Are you all right,
ma'am?

37:06.458 --> 37:08.558
I'm fine.

37:08.560 --> 37:11.261
[ breathing heavily ]

37:24.475 --> 37:26.910
[ pearls clatter ]

37:29.880 --> 37:32.449
[ sobbing ]
ma'am?

37:34.252 --> 37:35.752
[ sobbing ] leave me be.

37:35.754 --> 37:36.686
Just leave me be!

37:36.688 --> 37:38.521
Fitz: Mel?

37:38.523 --> 37:39.823
Mellie?

37:39.825 --> 37:41.458
[ crying ]

37:41.460 --> 37:43.727
Get out of here.

37:43.729 --> 37:46.563
I'm sorry.

37:46.565 --> 37:48.698
I'm so sorry.

37:48.700 --> 37:50.000
It's okay.

37:50.002 --> 37:51.434
It's over.

37:51.436 --> 37:52.736
It's over.

37:52.738 --> 37:54.537
I'm sorry.

37:54.539 --> 37:56.473
I'm so sorry.

37:56.475 --> 37:57.607
I'm so sorry.

37:57.609 --> 38:00.677
[ keyboard clacking ]

38:00.679 --> 38:03.847
[ <i>camera shutter clicking</i> ]

38:03.849 --> 38:05.882
[ computer beeping ]

38:21.999 --> 38:23.867
[ knock on door ]

38:27.838 --> 38:28.938
What's this?

38:28.940 --> 38:30.473
It's the '94 du bellay,

38:30.475 --> 38:32.475
The last bottle
from the island.

38:33.811 --> 38:35.679
You came over here
to give me a bottle of wine?

38:35.681 --> 38:37.080
I thought about
wearing a bikini,

38:37.082 --> 38:39.049
I thought about bringing
a coconut or a pineapple

38:39.051 --> 38:41.051
Or one of those cheesy
little bottles full of sand.

38:41.053 --> 38:43.586
But we're not
on the island.
No.

38:43.588 --> 38:44.788
And we're not standing
in the sun.

38:44.790 --> 38:46.056
No.

38:46.058 --> 38:48.091
This is not a booty call.
Okay.

38:48.093 --> 38:50.060
And if I want to summon you,
I will summon you.

38:50.062 --> 38:52.829
Olivia.
Come here to me.

38:52.831 --> 38:54.864
[ donna summer's
"macarthur park" plays ]

